&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch provides a truncate task for SAI that marks the index as queryable. There was a window of opportunity if the initial index build and table truncate operations were triggered concurrently where the index build was interrupted. This meant that index wasn&apos;t marking itself as queryable. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
